         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... to the ministers daughters were born, [and] to the kings. Certainly vessels full of pearls</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a1 #a2 #a3 #a4 #a5 #a6 #b1 #b2 #b3 #b4 #b5 #b6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:sieg1952"/><citedRange>22-23</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>121</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>116</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... ministers. The daughters of the kings are ready for a union, all other kings in Jambudvīpa</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1983"/><citedRange>20</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... The Bodhisattva sat silent, without paying attention. Thereupon the ministers, [with regard to] the one being loveless, say</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1952"/><citedRange>42</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1954"/><citedRange>716</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>139</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... to the king: Oh lord, if the prince should not succeed in leaving the house</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4 #a5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>266, 275</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1983"/><citedRange>40</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:knoll1996"/><citedRange>30</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... give him [your] permission! He shall leave the house. If he obtains pleasure in the forest, [then it is] good. Judicious ones</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">If he obtains pleasure in the forest, it [is] good.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>645</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... gib ihm die Erlaubnis! Er soll aus dem Hause gehen. Wenn er am Wald Gefallen findet, [dann ist es] gut.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">... give him permission! He shall go out of the house. If he takes delight in the wood, [it is] well.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>196</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>115</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>229</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1983"/><citedRange>40</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>80</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... who gave up kingship [and] went to the forest. But if</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... welche die Königswürde aufgaben [und] zum Walde gingen.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">... who [pl.] gave up royal dignity [and] went to the forest.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>417</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:knoll1996"/><citedRange>28</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... Also (for) the living there is (nothing) ... but father [and] mother.</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>240</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>246</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>82</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (Thereupon the king) says (heatedly) to the ministers: I have truly come to be deeply worried (?), because: || In the D.-</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>302</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>111, 144</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">(-tune: || ... if) I separate from [my] dear son. He was living in happiness, wrapped in a beggar’s garment</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (wenn) ich mich von [meinem] lieben Sohn trenne.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">... (when) I part from [my] dear son.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>278</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>214</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (If) I do (not) give him permission, he will starve himself. As if [caught] in a pair of tongs [I am] because of this suffering, (depressed in the heart) [and] in the belly.</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">If I do not let him go, he will starve himself out.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>637</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[Wenn] ich ihm (nicht) die Erlaubnis gebe, wird er von selbst verhungern [wtl. das Selbst verhungern lassen].</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">[If] I (do not) give him permission, he will starve himself [lit. will let [his] self starve].</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>314</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">(1. ... Give him permission!). Thereupon the king speaks to the ministers: So it shall be, [oh] skilful ones, if you</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">So it will be.  (cf 23)</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>624</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... permission the prince shall have. May he leave the house. The ministers thought: in that way the prince</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">… the prince will have permission: he may leave the house.  (cf 23)</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>219</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
